div.div:
Mhm, I might consider to add "Plugin"-like support to bokusu later on, and aniDB "support" can be installed separately and doing so, the user acknowledges the possibility of their account/IP get banned. Additionally, the scraper will give 2 options: send a POST native export feature to aniDB each month (to decrease possibility to get banned) and user will download it manually, or scrape mylist's html. The latter might have some issues regarding on how it displayed publicly. For now, I'm currently focusing on fixing base/core functions for bokusu then adding supports to services listed on a table. aniDB won't be listed as planned integration considering the risks outweigh the benefits and will be available as separate module.
[!NOTE] There's possibility that aniDB already blacklisted GitHub Action's IP addresses as bokusu also intended to be automatically run with CI, similar approach with https://github.com/Animanga-Initiative/animeManga-autoBackup.
